cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about deep learning methods for action recognition in videos, which is a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a new approach for end-to-end video-level representation learning, which involves training deep neural networks (cs.LG) with temporal pyramid pooling (cs.MM) to aggregate frame-level features. The paper also discusses the limitations of current methods and proposes solutions, which involves some level of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural network engineering (cs.NE).
